33:41.645 --> 33:42.895
Don , thanks again for the home run .

33:42.979 --> 33:44.897
- I love to come through .
- Speaking of which,

33:44.981 --> 33:47.191
any chance you could
patch things up with Rachel Menken?

33:47.275 --> 33:49.402
Any way you can be
as charming as I said you were?

33:49.486 --> 33:51.821
Haven't you had enough
of my magic for one day?

33:51.905 --> 33:54.281
She's worth $3 million .

33:54.366 --> 33:55.991
You're a whore.

33:58.704 --> 34:00.037
Peggy--

34:00.122 --> 34:02.081
Could she get us a little more ice?

34:02.165 --> 34:04.750
- Yes, Mr. Draper?
- Just a minute.

34:04.835 --> 34:06.919
Fellas, I think this party's gonna
have to move elsewhere.

34:07.003 --> 34:09.171
We'll move wherever you want, but it's 5: 1 5.

34:09.256 --> 34:10.673
The bachelor party's underway.

34:10.757 --> 34:11.924
I don't know.

34:12.008 --> 34:14.135
Oh, come on, Don . All hands on deck.

34:14.219 --> 34:15.928
Aren't you gonna help
give Pete his big sendoff?

34:16.012 --> 34:17.930
Maybe next time.

34:20.642 --> 34:21.600
Come on , guys.

34:21.685 --> 34:23.144
Don will join us later, right, Don?

34:31.820 --> 34:33.070
If Greta's research was any good ,

34:33.155 --> 34:34.363
I would have used it.

34:35.907 --> 34:37.533
What are you talking about?

34:37.617 --> 34:39.744
I'm saying I had a report just like that.

34:39.828 --> 34:42.371
And it's not like there's
some magic machine

34:42.456 --> 34:44.957
that makes identical copies of things.

34:46.042 --> 34:48.210
I still think she was right.

34:53.258 --> 34:55.801
Have a great night, Pete.

34:55.886 --> 34:56.886
Congratulations.

35:06.605 --> 35:09.148
I heard you were
amazing in the meeting .

35:09.232 --> 35:12.026
Fear stimulates my imagination .

35:14.070 --> 35:17.740
I just wanted to thank you
for a great first day,

35:17.824 --> 35:20.451
and for, you know. . .

35:20.535 --> 35:23.788
standing up for me with Mr. Campbell.

35:37.385 --> 35:39.011
First of all , Peggy,

35:39.095 --> 35:41.472
I'm your boss, not your boyfriend .

35:43.850 --> 35:46.352
Second of all, you ever let Pete Campbell
go through my trash again ,

35:46.436 --> 35:49.396
and you won't be able to find a job
selling sandwiches in Penn Station .

35:52.317 --> 35:55.027
He said he left his fountain pen in here.

35:55.111 --> 35:56.987
I didn't know.

36:00.575 --> 36:03.369
I hope you don't think
I'm that kind of girl.

36:03.453 --> 36:06.330
Of course not.

36:06.414 --> 36:08.833
Go home. Put your curlers in.

36:08.917 --> 36:10.960
We'll get a fresh start tomorrow.

36:12.546 --> 36:14.839
Oh . And , Peggy,

36:14.923 --> 36:16.215
I need you to place a call .

36:38.154 --> 36:40.072
I want to see you here every 1 5 minutes,

36:40.156 --> 36:42.116
whether you have drinks or not.

36:42.200 --> 36:43.325
Uh , every five minutes.

36:45.245 --> 36:47.538
Let's live here.

36:47.622 --> 36:49.081
Better do more than look tonight.

36:49.165 --> 36:50.708
Do you have a girlfriend, Salvatore?

36:50.792 --> 36:53.669
Come on . I'm Italian .

36:53.753 --> 36:55.629
Is there some kind of party here?

36:57.173 --> 36:58.924
How did you swing it?

36:59.009 --> 37:00.968
They work at the Automat.

37:01.052 --> 37:03.762
He pressed a button , and they came out.

37:03.847 --> 37:05.472
I hope we're not interrupting anything.

37:05.557 --> 37:07.099
Definitely not.

37:07.183 --> 37:09.184
Well, I have the best seat.
What are we drinking?

37:09.269 --> 37:11.562
More of whatever's
making you the way you are.

37:11.646 --> 37:13.105
I love this place.

37:13.189 --> 37:16.108
It's hot, loud , and filled with men .

37:16.192 --> 37:18.027
I know what you mean .

37:30.206 --> 37:32.374
Oh , my God . I can already feel it.

37:32.459 --> 37:35.127
I have a feeling you're like this all the time.

37:35.211 --> 37:36.587
I like to laugh.

37:36.671 --> 37:38.130
Is that right?

37:38.214 --> 37:40.132
Now, you stop that.

37:40.216 --> 37:41.675
You said you like to laugh .

37:41.760 --> 37:43.385
I mean it.

37:43.470 --> 37:45.137
It's-- It's too. . .

37:45.221 --> 37:46.931
Too delicious.

37:47.015 --> 37:49.350
Hey, I said stop it,
What do you think you're doing?

37:49.434 --> 37:51.143
You know exactly.

37:51.227 --> 37:52.978
U m , you know what, girls?

37:53.063 --> 37:54.146
I think we should go.

37:54.230 --> 37:55.230
Oh , come on .

37:55.315 --> 37:57.191
You're hurting me.

37:59.945 --> 38:01.445
I'll be good .

38:03.114 --> 38:05.115
Buy the girls whatever they want.

38:11.873 --> 38:13.707
So, uh , what do you fellas do?

38:13.792 --> 38:16.335
You're looking at the finest
ad men in New York.

38:16.419 --> 38:18.337
Hell, the world .

38:43.279 --> 38:46.198
For the lady, a special Mai Tai,

38:46.282 --> 38:48.033
and one whiskey neat.

38:52.497 --> 38:54.707
So. . .

38:54.791 --> 38:56.792
you're going to ply me with drinks

38:56.876 --> 38:59.294
and convince me what a terrible
mistake I'm making .

39:00.422 --> 39:02.089
That is quite a drink.

39:02.173 --> 39:05.259
You got in trouble, didn't you?

39:08.138 --> 39:09.388
I shouldn't have lost my temper,

39:09.472 --> 39:11.473
and I certainly
shouldn't have treated you

39:11.558 --> 39:12.850
like anything less than a client.

39:12.934 --> 39:14.893
Apology accepted .

39:16.521 --> 39:18.522
So you understand .

39:18.606 --> 39:20.399
Now I do.

39:20.483 --> 39:24.361
It was, uh, refreshing, really.

39:24.446 --> 39:29.033
I mean , actually hearing all the things
I always assumed people were thinking .

39:31.327 --> 39:33.328
Well, I'm not really as bad as all that.

39:35.415 --> 39:36.790
I was under a lot of pressure.

39:36.875 --> 39:39.293
Another account.

39:41.963 --> 39:43.630
Doesn't really matter.

39:43.715 --> 39:45.841
No, it doesn't.

39:50.513 --> 39:53.640
So, without making things worse,
can I ask you a personal question?

39:53.725 --> 39:57.269
Don't you want to get
a second drink in me first?

39:57.353 --> 39:58.562
Why aren't you married?

40:00.523 --> 40:02.399
Are you asking
what's wrong with me?

40:02.484 --> 40:04.735
It's just that you're
a beautiful, educated woman .

40:04.819 --> 40:07.029
Don't you think that getting married
and having a family

40:07.113 --> 40:08.655
would make you happier
than all the headaches

40:08.740 --> 40:10.282
that go along with . . .

40:10.366 --> 40:11.867
fighting people like me?

40:14.913 --> 40:16.830
If I weren't a woman,
I would be allowed

40:16.915 --> 40:19.458
to ask you the same question .

40:19.542 --> 40:21.043
And if I weren't a woman,

40:21.127 --> 40:24.546
I wouldn't have to choose
between putting on an apron

40:24.672 --> 40:28.717
and the thrill of making my father's store
what I always thought it should be.

40:28.802 --> 40:34.973
So that's it. You won't get married
because you find business to be a thrill .

40:35.058 --> 40:37.392
That and . . .

40:40.396 --> 40:42.481
I've never been in love.

40:42.565 --> 40:46.193
She won't get married
because she's never been in love.

40:46.277 --> 40:48.904
I think I wrote that once to sell nylons.

40:48.988 --> 40:53.158
For a lot of people,
love isn't just a slogan .

40:53.243 --> 40:54.368
Oh , you mean love.

40:54.452 --> 40:56.161
You mean the big
lightning bolt to the heart

40:56.246 --> 40:58.330
where you can't eat and you can't work

40:58.414 --> 41:04.545
and you just run off
and get married and make babies.

41:04.629 --> 41:08.590
The reason you haven't felt it
is because it doesn't exist.

41:08.675 --> 41:10.050
What you call love

41:10.135 --> 41:14.179
was invented by guys
like me to sell nylons.

41:15.431 --> 41:17.349
Is that right?

41:17.433 --> 41:19.059
I'm pretty sure about it.

41:20.645 --> 41:22.354
You're born alone,
and you die alone,

41:22.438 --> 41:24.648
and this world just drops
a bunch of rules on you

41:24.732 --> 41:26.066
to make you forget those facts,

41:26.151 --> 41:27.609
but I never forget.

41:29.529 --> 41:32.364
I'm living like there's no tomorrow. . .

41:32.448 --> 41:34.533
because there isn't one.

41:36.536 --> 41:39.496
I don't think I realized it until this moment,

41:41.166 --> 41:45.544
but it must be hard being a man , too.

41:46.796 --> 41:48.130
Excuse me?

41:49.883 --> 41:50.841
Mr. Draper--

41:50.925 --> 41:52.384
- Don .
- Mr. Draper,

41:52.468 --> 41:55.679
I don't know what it is
you really believe in ,

41:55.763 --> 42:02.811
but I do know what it feels like
to be out of place, to be disconnected ,

42:02.896 --> 42:05.564
to see the whole world
laid out in front of you

42:05.648 --> 42:08.150
the way other people live it.

42:08.234 --> 42:13.447
There is something about you
that tells me you know it, too.

42:18.578 --> 42:20.829
I don't know if that's true.

42:22.957 --> 42:25.292
You want another drink?

42:25.376 --> 42:27.419
No.

42:27.503 --> 42:30.881
But you can tell your boss
that you charmed me.

42:37.513 --> 42:39.681
So I guess we'll be
seeing each other again .

42:39.807 --> 42:45.020
I'll be back in the office Monday morning,
for a real meeting .

42:45.104 --> 42:47.105
I'd like that.

43:02.747 --> 43:04.456
We're not buying anything.

43:04.540 --> 43:06.792
Actually, for the first time today,

43:06.876 --> 43:09.086
I'm not selling anything .

43:09.170 --> 43:11.421
Does Peggy live here?

43:11.506 --> 43:12.547
Hold on.

43:24.894 --> 43:26.353
Do you know him?

43:28.564 --> 43:30.107
It's okay, Marjorie.
We work together.

43:31.776 --> 43:32.818
He's really drunk.

43:32.902 --> 43:35.028
It's okay, Marjorie.

43:37.573 --> 43:41.535
So. . .what are you doing?

43:41.619 --> 43:42.744
Nothing .

43:42.829 --> 43:46.206
Just, uh, sitting in my room
listening to records.

43:46.291 --> 43:48.250
I'm getting married on Sunday.

43:48.334 --> 43:50.419
I heard that.

43:52.672 --> 43:54.840
You must think I'm a creep.

43:57.468 --> 43:59.594
Why are you here?

44:08.938 --> 44:11.606
I wanted to see you tonight.

44:15.611 --> 44:17.529
Me?

44:17.613 --> 44:19.865
I had to see you .

44:29.542 --> 44:30.792
Marjorie?

44:30.877 --> 44:33.003
Yeah, Peg?

44:33.087 --> 44:35.088
I'm going to bed now.

46:00.800 --> 46:04.719
I called the office. They said you'd left.

46:08.015 --> 46:09.641
I didn't want to bother you .

46:09.725 --> 46:11.518
It's no bother.

46:11.602 --> 46:14.771
I just assumed you were staying
in the city again.

46:17.024 --> 46:19.443
There's a plate in the oven .

46:25.575 --> 46:27.534
Unless you're not hungry.

46:27.618 --> 46:28.785
I'm not.

46:32.748 --> 46:34.833
I'll be right back.

46:35.918 --> 46:37.169
Don't move.

